1. Impulse for electric projectile (charge $ze$):
$$\Delta p_{\rm el}=e\int_{-\infty}^\infty E_y(t)\,dt
=e\int\frac{ze\,\gamma b}{\bigl(b^2+(\gamma vt)^2\bigr)^{3/2}}\,dt.$$
Let $u=\gamma vt$, $dt=du/(\gamma v)$:
$$\Delta p_{\rm el}
=e\,ze\int\frac{\gamma b}{(b^2+u^2)^{3/2}}\frac{du}{\gamma v}
=\frac{ze^2b}{v}\int_{-\infty}^\infty\frac{du}{(b^2+u^2)^{3/2}}.$$
Use $\int_{-\infty}^\infty du/(b^2+u^2)^{3/2}=2/b^2$:
$$\Delta p_{\rm el}
=\frac{ze^2b}{v}\cdot\frac{2}{b^2}
=\frac{2ze^2}{v\,b}.$$

2. Impulse for monopole ($g$):
$$\Delta p_{\rm mon}
=e\int_{-\infty}^\infty E_z(t)\,dt
=e\int\frac{g\,v\gamma b}{(b^2+(\gamma vt)^2)^{3/2}}\,dt
=\frac{egv b}{v}\int\frac{du}{(b^2+u^2)^{3/2}}
=\frac{2eg}{b}.$$

3. Ratio of impulses:
$$\frac{\Delta p_{\rm mon}}{\Delta p_{\rm el}}
=\frac{2eg/b}{2ze^2/(v\,b)}
=\frac{v\,g}{z\,e},\qquad z=1\ (\text{proton}).$$

4. Stopping power ‚àù$(\Delta p)^2$, so
$$\frac{(dE/dx)_{\rm mon}}{(dE/dx)_{\rm p}}
=\Bigl(\frac{v\,g}{e}\Bigr)^2.$$

5. Dirac quantization $eg=\hbar/2\implies g/e=\hbar/(2e^2)$. Also $e^2=4\pi\alpha\hbar$:
$$\Bigl(\frac{v\,g}{e}\Bigr)^2
=v^2\frac{\hbar^2}{4e^4}
=v^2\frac{\hbar^2}{4(4\pi\alpha\hbar)^2}
=\frac{v^2}{64\pi^2\alpha^2}.$$

1. Mean energy losses:  
$$\langle dE/dx\rangle_1 = A\ln(\xi^2+1)+B,\qquad 
\langle dE/dx\rangle_2 = A\ln\left(\left(\frac{\xi}{\alpha}\right)^2+1\right)+B.$$

2. Difference:  
$$\Delta=\langle dE/dx\rangle_1-\langle dE/dx\rangle_2
= A\left[\ln(\xi^2+1)-\ln\left(\frac{\xi^2}{\alpha^2}+1\right)\right]
= A\ln\left(\frac{\xi^2+1}{\frac{\xi^2}{\alpha^2}+1}\right).$$

3. Average:  
\begin{align*}
\overline{\langle dE/dx\rangle}
&=\frac{1}{2}\left(\langle dE/dx\rangle_1+\langle dE/dx\rangle_2\right)\\
&=\frac{A}{2}\left[\ln(\xi^2+1)+\ln\left(\frac{\xi^2}{\alpha^2}+1\right)\right]+B\\
&=A\left[\frac{1}{2}\left(\ln(\xi^2+1)+\ln\left(\frac{\xi^2}{\alpha^2}+1\right)\right)+\eta\right].
\end{align*}

4. NœÉ condition:  
$$\Delta = N\,\sigma_{dE/dx},\qquad R=\frac{\sigma_{dE/dx}}{\overline{\langle dE/dx\rangle}}.$$

5. Solve for R:  
$$R=\frac{\Delta}{N\,\overline{\langle dE/dx\rangle}}
=\frac{A\ln\left(\frac{\xi^2+1}{\frac{\xi^2}{\alpha^2}+1}\right)}
{N\,A\left[\frac{1}{2}\left(\ln(\xi^2+1)+\ln\left(\frac{\xi^2}{\alpha^2}+1\right)\right)+\eta\right]}
=\frac{\ln\left(\frac{\xi^2+1}{\frac{\xi^2}{\alpha^2}+1}\right)}
{N\left[\frac{1}{2}\left(\ln(\xi^2+1)+\ln\left(\frac{\xi^2}{\alpha^2}+1\right)\right)+\eta\right]}\,. $$
